Author: Jamieson Christian
Subject: Not very user friendly
Body: This app is a study in poor UX design. The blank start screen offers no options, actions or instructions. There's no "open file" action, and the app does not inform other apps to use it to open SVG files. The end result is that you have to really know what you're doing to get this app to work for you. (For instance, I used ES File Explorer to open files in this app.) Once open, SVG files seem to render well enough; the starting zoom level was illogical, though.

Author: Emmet Caulfield
Subject: Views SVG, but "hijacks" file browser on Galaxy S III
Body: It seems to work fine as an SVG viewer on my Samsung Galaxy S III, but there doesn't appear to be any way to exit it!   Every time I open an SVG file from "My Files" (the default file browser), the SVG file displays just fine, but when I hit "Back", I get all the way back to the Home screen, not the file browser. If I try to use the file browser again, I just get the SVG file I was previously viewing. Hitting the menu key doesn't bring up anything. No amount of double-tapping on tap-and-holding brings up any option or button or icon. So, it effectively supplants the default file browser completely until I go into "Settings -> Application Manager -> SVG viewer" and "Force quit".  It seems to be a fine SVG viewer, but it is rendered unusable by this bug :(
